>1.) how much should i expect to pay for a RELIABLE vehicle--will $3000 do
>it?

Prices vary like you wouldn't believe and the effort of your search and how 
much you learn before hand will greatly affect the quality of camper you 
get. 3K is a ton of money to start with. I got my first westy for under 
$1,300 and drive it to Ohio and back the next weekend without trouble.

>2.) what should i look for in terms of reliability (models, years, 
>features,
>etc to avoid?), and

This article is good explaining the differences in years and what to look 
for and such:
http://www.busdepot.com/links.jsp#GUIDE

>3.) where is the best place to look for such a vehicle--CA is not out of 
>the
>question.

CA,AZ places that are warm and dry are best.

